@Node "Overview" "RunMPIndex.guide/Overview"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Quick overview
**************

@{b}MPIndex@{ub} is a tool for indexing AmigaGuide documents - similar to the
Windows Help Search facility.

@{b}MakeMPIndex@{ub} is used to generate the index.

@{b}RunMPIndex@{ub} can then be used to display a Gui which allows the index to
be view and specific nodes selected.

An example usage is:

Find help nodes in all guides except fred.guide which include the words
"help" and/or "gadget" in the text and "test" in the title.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "RunMPIndex.guide/Installation"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "Overview"
@Toc "Main"

Installation Instructions
*************************

The following files are included in this distribution and require
installing in one directory:

     COPYING           : GNU License
     Docs.Index        : Index to the docs
     MakeMPIndex       : Tool to make the index.
     MakeMPIndex.guide : Docs for MakeMPIndex.
     MPIndex52Src.lha  : Source code
     RunMPIndex        : Tool to display the index.
     RunMPIndex.info   : Icon
     RunMPIndex.guide  : This file
     IgnoreWord        : Example IgnoreWord file


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "RunMPIndex.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Parameters"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Software and Hardware required
******************************

OS3.0+ is required.

A fast processor is useful for some functions.


@EndNode

@Node "Parameters" "RunMPIndex.guide/Parameters"
@Next "Gadgets"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Shell parameters
****************

The following parameters can be supplied:


 @{" FROM         " Link "FROM"}          Input file
 @{" COMMAND=COMM " Link "COMMAND"}          Command to display help
 @{" PUBSCREEN/K  " Link "PUBSCREEN"}          Screen to display on

@{b}RunMPIndex@{ub} can also be run from Workbench - all parameters are taken as
there default values.


@EndNode

@Node "FROM" "RunMPIndex.guide/FROM"
@Next "COMMAND"
@Toc "Parameters"

FROM Parameter
==============

This parameter gives the name of the Index file generated by
@{b}MakeMPIndex@{ub}.

If not supplied then the default of Docs.Index is used.


@EndNode

@Node "COMMAND" "RunMPIndex.guide/COMMAND"
@Next "PUBSCREEN"
@Prev "FROM"
@Toc "Parameters"

COMMAND Parameter
=================

This gives the command to run when the @{"Show" Link "g-show"} gadget is pressed. %s is
used to substitute with the help node.

e.g. "rx 'address fred help %s'"

Will send "help nodename" to ARexx port fred when the Show gadget is
pressed.

If this parameter is not supplied then the internal AmigaGuide viewer
is used. This requires RunMPIndex.guide to be available.


@EndNode

@Node "PUBSCREEN" "RunMPIndex.guide/PUBSCREEN"
@Prev "COMMAND"
@Toc "Parameters"

PUBSCREEN Parameter
===================

This gives the name of the Public Screen to open the window on. If this
parameter is not supplied then the default public screen is used.


@EndNode

