@Node "g-all" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-all"
@Next "g-none"
@Prev "g-help"
@Toc "Gadgets"

All Gadget
==========

The selects all of the @{"Files" Link "g-files"}.

'A' is the keyboard equivalent.


@EndNode

@Node "g-none" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-none"
@Next "g-search"
@Prev "g-all"
@Toc "Gadgets"

None Gadget
===========

This selects none of the @{"Files" Link "g-files"}.

'O' is the keyboard equivalent.


@EndNode

@Node "g-search" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-search"
@Next "g-words"
@Prev "g-none"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Search Gadget
=============

This allows the input of search criteria for @{"words" Link "g-words"}.

Three types of search can be input.

   @{b}*@{ub} One word with no wild cards. The first word matching at the start
     of the input is selected. All words are displayed

   @{b}*@{ub} One word with wild cards. Only words matching the input are
     displayed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Multiple parts of words seperated by spaces. Only words which
     contain any of the word parts input are displayed.

'S' activates this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "g-words" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-words"
@Next "g-files"
@Prev "g-search"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Words Gadget
============

This shows in the words in the @{"nodes" Link "g-nodes"} in the selected @{"files" Link "g-files"}.

The first word is #? which shows all @{"nodes" Link "g-nodes"} in the selected @{"files" Link "g-files"}.

'W' and 'w' cycle through the list.


@EndNode

@Node "g-files" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-files"
@Next "g-subset"
@Prev "g-words"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Files Gadget
============

This shows all the files in the index. The @{"all" Link "g-all"} and @{"none" Link "g-none"} gadgets can be
used to select all or none of the files.

The files can be selected or unselected by clicking with the mouse.

A @{b}W@{ub} is shown if the selected @{"word" Link "g-words"} is in the selected file.

A @{b}*@{ub} is shown against the file which contains the selected @{"node" Link "g-nodes"}.


@EndNode

@Node "g-subset" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-subset"
@Next "g-nodes"
@Prev "g-files"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Subset Gadget
=============

This allows the input of search criteria for @{"nodes" Link "g-nodes"} titles.

Two types of search can be input.

   @{b}*@{ub} A single part word. All node titles which contain the input part
     word are displayed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Multiple parts of words. All nodes titles which contain all of the
     input part words are displayed.

'U' activates this gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "g-nodes" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-nodes"
@Next "g-show"
@Prev "g-subset"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Nodes Gadget
============

This displays the node titles of nodes held in the selected @{"files" Link "g-files"} which
contain the currently selected @{"word" Link "g-words"}.

'N' and 'n' cycle through the list.


@EndNode

@Node "g-show" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-show"
@Next "g-cancel"
@Prev "g-nodes"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Show Gadget
===========

This shows help on the selected @{"node" Link "g-nodes"}.

'H' is the keyboard equivalent.


@EndNode

@Node "g-cancel" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-cancel"
@Next "g-wordcount"
@Prev "g-show"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Cancel Gadget
=============

This closes the window.

'C' is the keyboard equivalent.


@EndNode

@Node "g-wordcount" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-wordcount"
@Next "g-nodecount"
@Prev "g-cancel"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Word Count Gadget
=================

This shows the number of @{"words" Link "g-words"} currently being displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "g-nodecount" "RunMPIndex.guide/g-nodecount"
@Prev "g-wordcount"
@Toc "Gadgets"

Node Count Gadget
=================

This shows the number @{"nodes" Link "g-nodes"} currently being displayed.


@EndNode

